## Runtime API

```ts
import { env } from "penv";     // blessed path — typed, inferred from schema

env.databaseUrl;
env.app.jwtSecret;
env.require("jwt-secret");       // throws a clear error if absent
```

Types come straight from `schema.ts` — no duplicated interfaces, no manual typings, and autocomplete on the nested namespaces.

### Compatibility forms

```ts
import "penv/config";           // zero-config: discovers .penv/, resolves NODE_ENV,
                                 // populates process.env — dotenv-shaped

import { config } from "penv";  // explicit
config({ env: process.env.NODE_ENV, path: ".penv" });
```

The typed `import { env }` surface is the recommended path. The side-effecting `import "penv/config"` form populates `process.env` and, like dotenv, must run *before* any module reads `process.env` — an ESM import-ordering caveat to keep in mind if you use it.

